text: Bradford West Gwillimbury is a town in Simcoe County, Ontario, Canada. It was founded in 1991 when the Town of Bradford was merged with parts of the Townships of West Gwillimbury and Tecumseth. According to the Canada 2021 Census, the town had a population of 42,880. Two highways run through the town: Highway 9 and Highway 400.
